The paper discusses the security and distributed nature of Blockchain, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). It also discusses the graph theoretical aspects of Blockchain, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of Smart Contracts and De-centralized Autonomous Organizations, which are related to databases and information systems, falling under the categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the future of Blockchain, which could potentially have implications for cybersecurity, falling under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
